[Maps of Nigeria can be seen at http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/nigeria.pdf and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3101013,6479.

According to Wikipedia, Adamawa is a state in northeastern Nigeria, with its capital at Yola. It was formed in 1991 from part of Gongola State with 4 administrative divisions namely: Adamawa, Ganye, Mubi and Numan. It is also the home of the American University of Nigeria in Yola. It is one of the 36 States which constitute the Federal Republic of Nigeria (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adamawa_State). - Mod.CP]

