[The preceding press reports originating in California are representative of the alarm caused by this incident and the general unawareness of many American citizens that a dangerous childhood disease could originate and spread from such a benign and unthreatening source as a Disneyland theme park. Unlike other outbreaks of measles in recent years, this Disneyland outbreak has the potential to rapidly affect unvaccinated children resident in many communities remote from initial site of infection. On the positive side, this incident may persuade the minority of Americans with unvaccinated children to change their attitude. Paradoxically the attenuated measles virus vaccine is one of the safest, if not the safest vaccine currently available for any human disease. - Mod.CP]

